  "title": "WELDER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Interpret blueprints, drawings, and measurements to plan layouts.</li><li>Weld small and large components such as copper plumbing, beams, and pipelines.</li><li>Use specialized machinery for industrial welding and oversee machines that perform the same job.</li><li>Maintain and repair all machinery.</li><li>Assess welded surfaces, structures and components to identify errors.</li><li>Follow and enforce strict safety regulations such as wearing heat-resistant gloves, protective masks, and safety shoes.</li><li>Monitor machinery for appropriate usage and temperature.</li><li>Weld components in flat, vertical, and overhead positions.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>A valid certificate in welding from an accredited institution is preferred.</li><li>Excellent knowledge of welding machinery, electrical equipment, and manual tools.</li><li>Ability to read and interpret blueprints and designs.</li><li>Outstanding attention to detail.</li></ul>",
